Project charter is a short formal document that is created at the start of a project, 
signed by the Sponsor and issued to a project manager, covering the basics, including objectives, methods, cost,stakeholders, that is essential for managing a project.
•	To Make a Clear Outline of the Project Objectives. 
•	To Give Comprehensive Details About the Project Scope. 
•	To Establish the Timeline of the Project. 
•	To Specify Any Roles and Responsibilities. 
•	To Give an Idea of the Project Approach. 
•	To Be Informed of the Change Control. 
•	To Clarify Issue Management. 
•	Make All Vital Contact Information Available.

